post_text:
Important Message from our Southwest Regional Team:

On July 23, 2020, Governor Ducey announced a new Executive Order, Open for Learning, directing all Arizona schools to use health metrics as to when schools may open for in-person learning. These metrics will be included in a framework developed by the Arizona Department of Public Health and Arizona Department of Education. We anticipate receiving the framework by August 7th. At this time, Imagine Schools is reviewing all components of the new Executive Order and will share an update with staff and families very soon. Remote learning for all Imagine students begins on August 5th as originally scheduled. The health and safety of our students and staff, as well as the academic growth and character development of each student, remain as our top priorities. Thank you for your continued support!
text:
Important Message from our Southwest Regional Team:

On July 23, 2020, Governor Ducey announced a new Executive Order, Open for Learning, directing all Arizona schools to use health metrics as to when schools may open for in-person learning. These metrics will be included in a framework developed by the Arizona Department of Public Health and Arizona Department of Education. We anticipate receiving the framework by August 7th. At this time, Imagine Schools is reviewing all components of the new Executive Order and will share an update with staff and families very soon. Remote learning for all Imagine students begins on August 5th as originally scheduled. The health and safety of our students and staff, as well as the academic growth and character development of each student, remain as our top priorities. Thank you for your continued support!

Meals on Wheels

In an effort to connect more of our families with meals during the school closures, we are launching a "Meals on Wheels" program beginning tomorrow morning, Tuesday, March 24th. This will run Monday-Friday for the duration of the closure. As a reminder, any students ages 18 and younger in the Coolidge community may receive the “Grab and Go” breakfast and lunches. Please review the locations and stop times below. Each bus will remain at the given locations for approximately 30 minutes.

Imagine Schools will still hand out meals on campus from 9:00-12:30 as well.

post_text: The Pinal County Junior Livestock Committee is working on a plan related to the closure of the livestock show at the Pinal County Fair. We will keep you updated as soon as we have further information. Thank you to Mr. Carpenter and all of our FFA students!
shared_text:
Pinal County Junior Livestock Committee
March 14 at 5:36 PM ·

Pinal County Junior Livestock first and foremost has an obligation to protect the youth and communities that we serve. Based on the Center for Disease Control and research available it is recommended that social distancing is recommended to mitigate the spread of the coronavirus disease (COVID-19).

With a heavy heart we are announcing that the PCJLC March 17-22, 2020 Livestock show has been cancelled. We recognize this is a major upset. Further actions will be taken to support exhibitors financially. The PCJLC Board is committed to finding financial solutions and options for the exhibitors.

Furthermore, the carcass awards ceremony is cancelled & results will be posted online (Monday at 3pm).

Please don’t panic-hold onto your animals, and we will communicate next steps on Tuesday evening. If you have any solutions, or recommendations please send to your member at large or to PCJUNIORLIVESTOCK@gmail.com as we value your feedback.

shared_text:
Imagine Coolidge Elementary
March 16 at 2:56 PM ·

Imagine Schools in Coolidge will be providing FREE meals!

Please review the list of Imagine Schools locations providing FREE Breakfast and Lunch for pick up starting March 17, 2020 until further notice. All students, 18 years and younger are welcome to partake in this program. These meals are provided through the federal National Student Lunch Program (NSLP) at no cost to you. Each bag/box will include one breakfast and one lunch meal per student. The student or child must be present to receive the meals. The meals may be picked up Monday – Friday between 9:00 am and 12:30 pm. Staff will be present to hand you the bagged meals. You do not have to exit your car.

Meals will be handed out at Imagine Coolidge Elementary School!

post_text: For Prep Parents: Our campus was not impacted from the water main break at the elementary school. We are in full session and running our regular early dismissal schedule.
shared_text:
Imagine Coolidge Elementary
February 5 at 9:38 AM ·

Attention Parents: We experienced a water main break and currently have no water. As a result, we are canceling school for the remainder of the day. A phone blast has been sent out with this information. Also, due to a power outage within the local area, we currently do not have internet, but are able to take incoming calls, (520) 723-5391. We will update you later today in regards to school tomorrow. Bus transportation will start at 10:15 If you do not want your child to ride this bus, please call the school by 10:00. Thank you for your understanding and support.

post_text:
Our Middle School wrestling team competed in the Canyon Athletic Association state middle school wrestling championship placing 5th out of 14 teams!!!

IPC had two individual champions: Jonathan Y. placing 1st and Matthew M. placing 1st at heavyweight.
Nicolas S. placed 2nd, Sila P. was 2nd at heavyweight and Cody W. placed 4th.

Way to Go EAGLES! #EagleNation #CoachDuran,Jr
